Vice President Mike Pence discusses the federal government's response to Hurricane Irma in Central Florida and Puerto Rico. He commends the leadership of Governor Rick Scott in Florida and the progress that has been made in restoring infrastructure. Pence assures that FEMA assistance is available to those who need it and encourages citizens to apply for federal support. He also addresses the relief efforts in Puerto Rico, acknowledging the challenges but emphasizing the progress being made. Pence responds to criticism of the federal government's response, stating that resources are being allocated and support is being provided. He encourages viewers to donate to National Volunteer Organizations and provides information on how to do so. Pence concludes by expressing the commitment of the federal government to help Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands recover.